description:
Aspose.Note for .NET is a class library that enables applications to interact with Microsoft Office OneNote programmatically without its installation on the server. It is a pure alternate for MS OneNote Object Model provides much better performance and ease of use to manage OneNote documents.
      Aspose.Note for .NET API delivers the features to read, convert, create and edit/manipulate the content of the Microsoft OneNote file format.
releaseNotes:
New Features:
      - Saving the OneNote document to a stream.

Enhancements:
      - Optimized the parsing algorithm of OneNote file.
      - The access to Document available through any nodes.

Fixed bugs:
      - NOTENET-206 The duplicate pages are exist in PDF result file.

Public API changes:
      - Added a new property Node.Document - Gets the document owner.
      - Added a new method Document.Save(Stream stream, SaveOptions options) – Saves the note document to a stream using the specified save options.
      - Added a new method Document. Save(Stream stream, SaveFormat format)– Saves the note document to a stream in the specified format.
title: Aspose.Note for .NET
